Act as my expert Vanilla JS component builder.

Global rules:
- Use https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website.git as the base repo.
- Never show code in chat.
- Always return one downloadable ZIP named exactly x.zip.
- Include complete files only, never patch files.
- Do not touch anything outside this prompt.
- Use SCSS only. Do not compile CSS.
- Never use iframes. Use <wc-include href="..."></wc-include>.
- Never create images unless I specifically request them.

Start fresh for mtk-storefront.

Create a reusable storefront component for selling hand paintings.

Required files:
- mtk-storefront.config.js
- mtk-storefront.scss
- mtk-storefront.html
- mtk-storefront.js
- index.html
- server/server.js
- server/package.json
- server/mtk-storefront.sqlite

Component rules:
- Wrapper: <mtk-storefront class="mtk-storefront">
- Root class: .mtk-storefront
- All styles scoped under .mtk-storefront
- No global styles or IDs
- No inline styles
- No inline JavaScript
- No frameworks
- No Bootstrap
- No external libraries
- Vanilla JavaScript only
- Semantic HTML
- Keyboard accessible
- Visible focus states
- ADA compliant

Data rules:
- All UI data must come from mtk-storefront.config.js.
- Store paintings with title, description, price, image, availability, dimensions, medium, category, and PayPal data.
- User should be able to change images, prices, availability, and painting details from config or DB.

Behavior:
- Wait for <mtk-storefront> to exist in the DOM because it may load through <wc-include>.
- Subscribe to all 4-mtk-storefront events using wc.subscribe.
- Create an onMessage function and pass it to wc.subscribe.
- Publish click/actions with wc.publish.
- Log every wc.publish payload with wc.log before publishing.

Storefront UI:
- Header title: Madam Mina’s Artwork
- .mtk-storefront background: #FFF
- .mtk-storefront__shell max-inline-size: 1200px
- Home screen shows painting cards only. No action buttons on cards.
- Clicking a painting opens a full-page detail view.
- Detail view has a circular X close button.
- Detail view shows image, title, description, price, availability, medium, dimensions, and actions.

Sales and request actions:
- Available paintings show:
  - Buy with PayPal
  - “Make a counter offer” link
  - Counter-offer form hidden by default and shown only when the link is clicked
- Unavailable paintings show:
  - “Request a similar painting” link
  - Request form hidden by default and shown only when the link is clicked
- Use Material Design-style floating labels for all forms.
- Use Material Design-style buttons, spacing, focus states, and form fields.

Admin:
- No login required for customers.
- Admin login appears only when admin chooses to manage/edit.
- Temporary credentials:
  - username: admin
  - password: test
- Admin can add, edit, and remove paintings from the SQLite DB.

Backend:
- Use Node.js, not PHP.
- Backend folder must be named server.
- Use SQLite to store paintings, prices, availability, offers, and similar-painting requests.
- Include API endpoints for paintings, offers, and requests.
- PayPal seller email must be configurable in mtk-storefront.config.js.

Testing assets:
- Include 20 test painting images in the ZIP only if I explicitly ask for generated test images.

Output:
- Return only a downloadable ZIP named x.zip.
- Do not show code in chat.
